## Runbook 1: WebSocket Disconnect / Stale Order Book

**Symptoms**: Bot not receiving book updates, OBI readings unchanged for > 60s, WS error in logs

```bash
# Step 1: Check WS connection status in logs
docker logs kalshi-bot --tail=100 | grep -E "websocket|WS|disconnect|reconnect"

# Step 2: Check if auto-reconnect is running
docker logs kalshi-bot --tail=50 | grep -E "Retry|reconnect attempt"

# If auto-reconnect appears stuck (same error > 5 minutes):
# Step 3: Restart just the bot container (preserves DB state)
docker restart kalshi-bot
sleep 30
docker logs kalshi-bot --tail=30 | grep "WebSocket connected"

# Step 4: If still failing, check Kalshi exchange status
curl -s "https://trading-api.kalshi.com/trade-api/v2/exchange/status" | python3 -m json.tool

# Step 5: If exchange is down, set bot to PAUSE_ENTRIES mode
docker exec kalshi-bot python -c "
from tools.admin_cli import bot_control
bot_control.set_mode('PAUSE_ENTRIES')
print('Bot paused — will resume when WS reconnects')
"

# Step 6: Log the incident
echo "[$(date -u)] SEV-2: WS disconnect. Auto-reconnect failed. Manual restart at $(date -u). Exchange status: [OK/DOWN]" >> /var/log/kalshi/incidents.log
```

