## Runbook 2: Stuck Open Position (Cannot Close)

**Symptoms**: Exit order submitted but not filling, position open past expected hold time, fill errors in logs

```bash
# Step 1: Identify the stuck position
docker exec kalshi-bot python -c "
from kalshi.client import KalshiClient
from kalshi.auth import KalshiAuth
import os
client = KalshiClient(KalshiAuth(os.getenv('KALSHI_API_KEY_ID'), os.getenv('KALSHI_PRIVATE_KEY_PATH')))
positions = client.get_positions()
print(positions)
"

# Step 2: Cancel any pending exit orders
docker exec kalshi-bot python -c "
from tools.admin_cli import order_manager
order_manager.cancel_all_open()
print('All pending orders canceled')
"

# Step 3: Check contract expiry — if < 5 min, do nothing and let it settle
# Kalshi will settle the contract and PnL will resolve automatically

# Step 4: If contract has time remaining, force close with aggressive (taker) pricing
docker exec kalshi-bot python -c "
from tools.admin_cli import position_manager
position_manager.force_close(reason='INCIDENT_MANUAL_CLOSE', aggressive=True)
"

# Step 5: If API rejects all close attempts, check for:
#   - INSUFFICIENT_FUNDS (can't buy back at current price)
#   - MARKET_CLOSED (contract expired — settlement will handle it)
#   - RATE_LIMITED (wait 30s, retry)
docker logs kalshi-bot --tail=50 | grep -E "rejection|REJECTED|error"

# Step 6: Record outcome
echo "[$(date -u)] SEV-1: Stuck position on [TICKER]. Closed via [method] at [price]. PnL: [amount]" >> /var/log/kalshi/incidents.log
```

