## Runbook 4: Bot Process Crashed / Won't Restart

**Symptoms**: Watchdog alert fires, container not running, heartbeat stale

```bash
# Step 1: Check container status and exit code
docker ps -a | grep kalshi-bot
docker inspect kalshi-bot --format='{{.State.ExitCode}} {{.State.Error}}'

# Step 2: Check for OOM kill (out of memory)
docker inspect kalshi-bot --format='{{.State.OOMKilled}}'
# If true → memory issue. Check usage before restart:
free -h && docker stats --no-stream

# Step 3: Check last logs before crash
docker logs kalshi-bot --tail=100 2>&1 | tail -50

# Step 4: Restart the container
docker compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d bot
sleep 30

# Step 5: Verify health
docker inspect --format='{{.State.Health.Status}}' kalshi-bot
docker logs kalshi-bot --tail=30

# Step 6: If crash is repeating (3+ times in 30 min):
# STOP and investigate before restarting again
# Pull most recent logs to local for analysis
docker logs kalshi-bot > /tmp/crash_$(date +%Y%m%d_%H%M%S).log 2>&1
# DO NOT keep force-restarting a repeatedly crashing bot — it may be in a bad state

echo "[$(date -u)] Bot crash. Exit code: [N]. OOM: [Y/N]. Restarted at: [time]. Status: [OK/INVESTIGATING]" >> /var/log/kalshi/incidents.log
```

